  "dcterms:abstract": "Niche signals maintain stem cells in a prolonged quiescence or transiently activate them for proper regeneration. Altering balanced niche signalling can lead to regenerative disorders. Here, using genetic mouse models, we show that dermal clusters of senescent melanocytes drive epithelial hair stem cells to exit quiescence and enhance hair renewal through the signalling factor osteopontin.",
